article.headline: Brown 77, Dartmouth 54
article.story: PROVIDENCE, R.I. (AP) -- Patrick Powers scored 25 points to lead Brown to a 77-54 win over Dartmouth on Friday night. Jason Forte had a triple-double for the Bears, scoring 11 points, pulling down 12 rebounds, and adding 10 assists. Mike McLaren scored 12 points to lead Dartmouth (3-22, 1-10 Ivy). Brown (12-12, 8-3) set the tone early, scoring the first 14 points of the game and taking a 21-3 lead with 12:45 left in the first half. The Big Green cut the lead to nine points to 33-24 on Mike McLaren's 3-pointer with 5:27 remaining in the half. The Bears scored on a Mike Martin 3-pointer and a driving lay-up by Forte in the final 1:22 to take a 40-29 halftime lead. Martin scored 15 points for the Bears and Jaime Kilburn added 14. Brown started the second half with another rally, outscoring the Big Green 16-4 in the opening 7:52 to take a 56-33 lead with 12:08 to play. Back-to-back 3-pointers by Michael Lang and McLaren allowed Dartmouth to pull to 56-40 with 10:16 left. But Brown responded with 10 unanswered points, taking a 66-40 lead with 7:32 remaining. With the win, Brown kept its hold on second place in the Ivy League while Dartmouth dropped its 15th straight game.
